    "description": "Toyo Shutter Co., Ltd. manufactures, installs, purchases, imports, sells, and exports various shutters, doors, hardware, and building fixtures, materials, and consumables in Japan. The company offers heavy-duty, lightweight, aluminum, and high-speed sheet shutters; overdoor; hangar door; disaster prevention products; building materials; butterfly stop; and other products. It also provides steel, front, and special doors; residential overdoors; locks, hardware, cylinder type, and cutaway view products. In addition, the company offers architectural hardware, marine equipment/decorative hardware, and furniture and kitchen equipment, as well as disaster, crime, and flood prevention equipment. Additionally, it engages in the design, supervision, contracting, and execution of architecture and facility construction; design and construction of electrical equipment work; development of computer software; sale of computer equipment; sale, installation, and repair of machinery, equipment, and materials for various types of electric transportation and electrical equipment; and buying, selling, leasing, brokerage, and management of real estate. Further, the company is involved in outdoor advertising; maintenance work; acquisition, rental, and sale of industrial property rights, copyrights and other intangible property rights, know-how, system engineering, and other software; non-life insurance agency business; automobile liability insurance agency business; and business related to solicitation of life insurance. Toyo Shutter Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1955 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan."
